912. Menaechmus is in a very bad temper, owing to his adventures during the after- noon, and therefore returns a somewhat rough answer to the inquiries of the officious quaok.

913. ‘This case cannot be cured with an ointment of hellebore'. The observation is of course addressed to the old man, and not to Menaechmus. Heuebore was used as a sove- reign remedy against insanity. See Hor. Sat. 11 3, 82 sq. Ep.
